        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Column radiators for Formby period rooms</strong><p>Traditional steel column radiators in two, three and four column configurations for Freshfield and Formby Village period properties. Available up to 1800mm in height, correct for high-ceilinged period reception rooms. Sized by BTU requirement first, column configuration second.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Designer and vertical radiators</strong><p>For Formby open plan areas or kitchen extensions where horizontal wall space is limited. We advise on output requirements before supply, vertical designer radiators with low surface area can underperform in large Formby open plan rooms if not correctly specified.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Bathroom towel rails</strong><p>Chrome, white and anthracite finishes. Connected to the central heating circuit or dual fuel versions for Formby bathrooms where independent operation is preferred. G3 qualified engineers available for properties with unvented cylinders.</p></div></div>
