    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">Radiators Formby. Your Questions Answered</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Straight answers to what Formby homeowners ask most before booking.</p>
      <div class="pf-faq">
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">COST</span>&nbsp; How much does radiator installation cost in Formby?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A new radiator supply and fit costs from £200, including the radiator, TRV, all fittings and system balancing. Labour only for a like-for-like replacement costs from £80. TRV upgrades cost from £50 per valve. Column and designer radiators are priced on quotation based on the specific style and size required. All prices are fixed. Quote visits are free, we do not charge for them.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">SIZING</span>&nbsp; My Formby sitting room has always been cold. How do I know if the radiator is undersized?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A room that is always cold despite the heating running is almost always caused by an undersized radiator. We calculate the BTU requirement for the room at the quote visit, this accounts for room dimensions, ceiling height, glazing area and insulation. We then confirm whether the existing radiator meets that requirement. In our experience, a significant proportion of large Formby reception rooms have radiators that are undersized. The free quote visit will tell you definitively.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">COLUMN</span>&nbsp; Can you fit column radiators in Formby period properties?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. Column radiators are excellent in Freshfield and Formby Village period rooms with high ceilings and bay windows. We specify the column height and configuration based on the BTU requirement for the room, the aesthetic choice comes second to the heating performance requirement. We route pipework under suspended timber floors where possible to maintain the period aesthetic. Column radiators are available in heights up to 1800mm.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">EXTENSION</span>&nbsp; Can you add a radiator to my Formby kitchen extension?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. We assess the pipe route, the existing system boiler capacity and the correct BTU requirement for the new room at the quote visit. For multi-zone Formby systems, we also confirm the correct zone assignment for the new radiator and how the zone thermostat should be set to include the new room. This is a straightforward job but the zone configuration check is essential and is often overlooked by general plumbers unfamiliar with multi-zone systems.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-green">GAS SAFE</span>&nbsp; Are you Gas Safe registered for Formby radiator installation?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. All radiator work connecting to the central heating circuit is carried out by our own directly employed Gas Safe registered engineers. Verify at <a href="https://www.gassaferegister.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gassaferegister.co.uk</a>. We never use sub-contractors.</p></div></details>
